  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a single axis coordinate in a variable font variation position.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate` pairs a variation axis tag with a value, specifying the position along that axis in design space. Use an array of these with <see cref="M:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(System.ReadOnlySpan{SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate})" /> or <see cref="P:SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments.VariationDesignPosition" /> to create a typeface at a specific design position.

## Examples

```csharp
var coords = new[]
{
    new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"), Value = 700f },
    new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("ital"), Value = 1f }
};
using var typeface = original.Clone(coords);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
